### Minor (Tightening) — not applied

1. **Diagnosis → Childhood.** The diagnosis section ends on "bracing for the other shoe"; the childhood section opens cold with "Keira Knightley exists because of a wager." The genre convention carries it, but no keyword bridges the gap. A clause at the start of the wager paragraph tying the bracing to its origin (e.g., that the bracing was installed before she could read — language the section already uses) would make it explicit.
2. **Childhood → Fights.** "Start the catalogue in 2004" reaches back two sections for its antecedent (the diagnosis section's "one repeated maneuver"). The childhood section ends on the tender dollhouse beat, then pivots abruptly to the King Arthur poster. One sentence carrying "vigilance" from the deal into the adult catalogue would close the seam.
3. **Fights → Breakdown.** The fights section ends "The engine underneath is protection"; the breakdown section explains what made protection necessary but never says so. A half-sentence noting that the protection was earned, not theoretical, would convert an adequate transition into a strong one.
4. **Internal, fights section.** The chronology jumps 2018 ("The Weaker Sex") back to 2007 (Daily Mail). It works thematically because "she keeps filing corrections" hands off to a literal lawsuit filing, but a reader tracking dates may bump. Lowest priority of the four.

